<h2>Nine Days On Yggdrasil</h2>
<p>Nine Days On <a href="inner#yggdrasil_en" rel="clearbox[tnhrf=nopreview,,title=Yggdrasil]">Yggdrasil</a> <dfn id="yggdrasil_en">In Scandinavian mythology Yggdrasil is the World Tree, or the tree of life. According to the Mongolians the World Tree is just a simple rod which gods use to tie their horses to it. For the Jakuts the Tree grows on top of the golden belly button of the Earth and the first people were born there, at its foot. Tanguz people say that the souls of the yet unborn children pass their time among the branches in the form of little birds. The Turkish believe that the World Tree has one million leaves with someone’s life on each leaf, and if a leaf falls down the person dies. Odin, the chief god in Scandinavian mythology was hanging from Yggdrasil pierced by a spear for nine days to get to know the secrets of poetry and the runes. (His knowledge made Odin mournful and melancholic.)</dfn> is a conceptual musical experiment that is about obsessions with the real essence of poetry, getting away from community, the paradox of the possibility of enlightenment and the nature of the ego. At the end of the story one thinks it over and goes for a new direction: one has to find the way back to community (again) and learn to love (again).</p>
<div class="tracks"></div>
<p>All music written and performed by MNG (guitars, bass, keyboard, samplers, and programming)<br />Text in Apocalyptic Poetry by <a href="inner#veronica_lueken_en" rel="clearbox[tnhrf=nopreview,,title=Veronica Lueken]">Veronica Lueken</a> <dfn id="veronica_lueken_en">I'm suspended<br />And the light is so bright it hurts my eyes<br />And I see this huge ball<br />Now in the center its...<br />Its A gray colored ball<br />Almost.. oh... I don't know what its made of...<br />But the rock like formation<br />But as its turning now<br />Its begining to change color<br />Becoming a purplish Hazy Orange looking ball...</dfn></p>

